==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overhead expenses
<hw>O`ver*head" expenses</hw>,
etc. }</mhw> <fld>(Accounting)</fld> <def>Those general charges or
expenses in any business which cannot be charged up as belonging
exclusively to any particular part of the work or product, as where
different kinds of goods are made, or where there are different
departments in a business; -- called also <altname>fixed
charges</altname>, <altname>establishment charges</altname>, or (in a
manufacturing business) <altname>administration charges</altname>,
<stype>selling charges</stype>, and <stype>distribution charges</stype>,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overhear</ent>⟦br⟧
